ootball Wins Night + 'SpongeBob SquarePants', 'Sanjay & Craig', 'Attack on Titan' & More|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|publisher=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = \n|LineColor       = FF6229\n}}\n{{Episode List\n|EpisodeNumber   = 40\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n|Title           = Wings of Fire\n|DirectedBy      = Peder Pedersen\n|WrittenBy       = John Derevlany\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|11|22}}\n|Viewers         = 1.59<ref name=\"Kondolojy\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/11/04/saturday-cable-ratings-college-football-wins-night-spongebob-squarepants-sanjay-craig-attack-on-titan-more/323494/|title=Saturday Cable Ratings: College Football Wins Night + 'SpongeBob SquarePants', 'Sanjay & Craig', 'Attack on Titan' & More|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|publisher=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = \n|LineColor       = FF6229\n}}\n{{Episode List\n|EpisodeNumber   = 41\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n|Title           = The Heart of Cavora\n|DirectedBy      = Peder Pedersen\n|WrittenBy       = John Derevlany\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|11|22}}\n|Viewers         = 1.59<ref name=\"Kondolojy\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/11/04/saturday-cable-ratings-college-football-wins-night-spongebob-squarepants-sanjay-craig-attack-on-titan-more/323494/|title=Saturday Cable Ratings: College Football Wins Night + 'SpongeBob SquarePants', 'Sanjay & Craig', 'Attack on Titan' & More|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|publisher=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = \n|LineColor       = FF6229\n}}\n|}\n\n==Mini Movies==\nA series of Mini Movies of extra adventures in the land of CHIMA were uploaded on the Lego website and YouTube channel. A selection of them appeared on special Season 1 Part 1 DVD releases.\n\n==Crossover==\n===Lego Ninjago===\n1.\nIn the [[Lego Ninjago]]: [[Masters of Spinjitzu]] [[List of Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu episodes#ep54|episode 54 Curseworld Part II]], the realm of Chima appears to be one of the many multiple realms alongside with the realm of Ninjago. When Lloyd and Morro have teleported themselves there with the Realm Crystal, surprises the local population, before teleporting themselves away and leaving a shocked Laval behind them.\n\n\n\n\n\n2.\nIn The [[Lego Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu]] [[List of Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu episodes#ep125|episode 126 The Kaiju Protocol ]], The Beavers of [[Legends of Chima]] Appear After Master Wu and P.I.X.A.L Opened A Portal Trying to Reach the Ninjas in the Never Realm by the Help of Mistaki's Travelers Tea\n\n==Cast==\n*David Attar - Cragger, Lennox, Rogon, Ripnik, Reegull, Stealthor\n*Bethany Brown - Eris, Crooler, Spinlyn, Rinona, Wonald\n*Matt Cronander - Willhurt, Ewar, Elon\n*Bill Courage - Crominus, Lagravis, Longtooth, Lavertus, Mottrot\n*Chris Durchand - Dom De La Woosh, Sir Fangar, Strainor\n*Jesse Inocalla - Plovar, Grumlo, Runk, Sparracon, Fluminox\n*Meghan Kinsley - Crunket, G'Loona, Windra, Li'ella, Maula\n*John Nelson - Wakz, Crug, Balkar, Rukus, Flinx\n*Michael Patric - Gorzan, Scorm, Mungus, Voom Voom, Eglor\n*Scott Shantz - Laval, Worriz, Skinnet, Furtivo, Razcal, Sparratus, Scolder, Scutter, Lundor, Vardy, Firox\n*Jeff Evans Todd - Razar, Bladvic, Crawley, Winzar, Leonidas, Equila, Ewald\n*Adam White - Foltrax, Vornon, Tormak\n\n==Crew==\n*[[Doug Parker (voice actor)|Doug Parker]] - Voice Director\n\n==Ratings==\nThe series premiere was watched by 1.5 million viewers, making it the 10th highest rated show overall on cable that night.\n\n==Awards==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominee\n! Result\n|-\n| [[Banff Rockie Award]] || Best Branded Entertainment || M2Film<br>[[Lego]] || {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Banff Rockie Award]] || Breakthrough Entertainment Award of Excellence in Kids Animation || M2Film<br>[[Lego]] || {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Cam\u00e9ra d'Or|Gold Camera]] || Entertainment - Children's || Tommy Andreasen <br> John Derevlany <br> Erik Legernes <br> Phil McCormick <br> M2Film <br> [[Lego]] || {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe music for Legends of Chima was written by Danish composer [[Anthony Lledo]] who had worked together with [[Peder Pedersen (director)|Peder Pedersen]] on the director's Indiana Jones and Star Wars themed Lego shorts. The music was awarded the 2013 Cue Award for Best Television Score and has been released on two soundtrack albums by [[MovieScore Media]].\n\n''[[Legends of Chima (soundtrack)|Legends of Chima]]'' (Released 2013)\n{{Track listing\n|total_length = 31:50\n|title1 = Laval the Lion\n|length1 = 3:17\n|title2 = Chi\n|length2 = 2:40\n|title3 = Playful Tribes\n|length3 = 2:36\n|title4 = The Croc Swamp\n|length4 = 3:04\n|title5 = Cragger\n|length5 = 2:37\n|title6 = Speedor Races\n|length6 = 2:10\n|title7 = When We Were Kids\n|length7 = 2:12\n|title8 = Rhinos\n|length8 = 1:51\n|title9 = The Warrior Within\n|length9 = 2:26\n|title10 = Forever Rock\n|length10 = 2:14\n|title11 = Drums Of Chima\n|length11 = 1:30\n|title12 = The Big Battle\n|length12 = 2:20\n|title13 = The Great Story\n|length13 = 2:53\n}}\n\n''[[Legends of Chima Vol. 2 (soundtrack)|Legends of Chima Vol. 2]]'' (Released 2015)\n{{tracklist\n|total_length    = 31:00\n|title1          = Return of the Heroes\n|length1         = 3:32\n|title2          = Into the Outlands\n|length2         = 3:16\n|title3          = The Dark Tribes\n|length3         = 4:19\n|title4          = Ancient Hunters\n|length4         = 3:02\n|title5          = The Phoenix\n|length5         = 3:27\n|title6          = Hills of Chima\n|length6         = 2:50\n|title7          = Lavertus\n|length7         = 3:28\n|title8          = Frozen Land\n|length8         = 2:21\n|title9          = The Tale of Tormak\n|length9         = 3:30\n|title10         = Victory\n|length10        = 2:13\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n